FED is in a sticky situation. He''s pausing, likely due to bond market pressures and his own inflation goals. But there''s a twist. Other Fed members aren''t fully on board with his hawkish vibes. Powell''s emerging as the main hawk in the flock.

Market-wise? I''m betting on new Bull Market start earlier than most individuals, by mid-2024. The only hiccup might be a dip to the S&P''s 4300s or even 4200 before a surge.

History shows that post-Fed rate hike pauses, there''s usually a flood of liquidity into markets after about 12-15 months. But this time? I sense it''ll be quicker, maybe 6-9 months.

