Short term yields are high as compared to long-term so there is no incentive for banks to lend, however, I think we are at an inflection point for this process to change right now. Normally when the Fed pauses, you see a yields fall, the only reason yields are heated right now is because markets have not expected an extended pause after Powell''s statements yesterday.

